name: Pool
description: The Germantown YWCA pool was one of the most popular attractions within the building ever since its establishment.
imagetitle: Betty Shreiner conducts the first swimming class for teenagers at the Germantown YWCA swimming pool for the Junior Girls Day Camp in 1947.

name: Club Room
description: 1973-1975: Bottom club rooms were used for the Parent Cooperative Nursery School

name: Gym
description: The YWCA gymnasium, located across two floors, has served as a venue for numerous programs over the years, including aerobics classes, dance lessons, and various special events.
imagetitle: An exercise class at the Germantown YWCA

name: Lounge
description: First floor lounges were common gathering places for community members and were constantly busy with people meeting and talking.
imagetitle: Women form an assembly line at the Germantown YWCA

name: Lobby
imagetitle: Sailors and their sweethearts dance at the Germantown YWCA
